							<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How long does gastric bypass recovery take?</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-700">
								Gastric bypass patients typically stay in hospital for <strong>2-3 nights</strong>. Return to light activities occurs within 2-3 weeks, with return to work at 3-4 weeks for desk jobs and 6-8 weeks for physical work. Full recovery takes approximately <strong>8-12 weeks</strong>. The recovery is longer than gastric sleeve due to intestinal rerouting.
							</p>
