						<!-- FAQ 4 -->
						<div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6">
							<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">What's the difference between gastric bypass and gastric sleeve?</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-700">
								Gastric bypass creates a small stomach pouch and reroutes the intestine, achieving <strong>70-80% weight loss</strong> and excellent diabetes outcomes. Gastric sleeve removes 80% of the stomach, achieving 60-70% weight loss with simpler surgery and faster recovery. Bypass is better for diabetes and severe obesity, whilst sleeve has fewer complications and no malabsorption issues. <a href="/compare/gastric-sleeve-vs-gastric-bypass" class="text-green-600 hover:underline">See full comparison</a>.
							</p>
