						<div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6">
							<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Will I develop dumping syndrome after gastric bypass?</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-700">
								Dumping syndrome affects <strong>10-30%</strong> of gastric bypass patients. It occurs when food moves too quickly from the stomach to the small intestine, causing nausea, cramping, diarrhoea, and dizziness. It's typically triggered by high-sugar or high-fat foods. Most patients learn to manage it through diet modifications, and symptoms often improve over time.
